Synthetic IBDP-like Dataset

SynthIB.Rd

A small synthetic dataset of four students, illustrating the columns needed for typical IBDP pass/fail rules (CAS, total points, HL/SL sums, etc.).

Usage

SynthIB

Format

A data frame with 4 rows and 10 columns:

student_id

Unique ID string for each student.

CAS_met

Logical indicating whether CAS requirement is fulfilled.

Total

Numeric: total points across 6 subjects + any core points.

lowest_grade

Numeric: lowest subject grade (1–7).

count_2

Number of subjects scored as 2.

count_3orbelow

Number of subjects scored 3 or below.

HL_sum

Sum of the top 3 HL scores.

SL_sum

Sum of SL scores.

n_HL

Number of HL subjects taken.

n_SL

Number of SL subjects taken.

Examples

# Load the dataset
data("SynthIB")
head(SynthIB)
#>   student_id CAS_met Total lowest_grade count_2 count_3orbelow HL_sum SL_sum
#> 1       S001    TRUE    25            3       0              1     12     11
#> 2       S002    TRUE    20            2       1              2      8     10
#> 3       S003   FALSE    27            4       0              0     15     10
#> 4       S004    TRUE    30            4       0              0     15     12
#>   n_HL n_SL
#> 1    3    3
#> 2    3    3
#> 3    3    3
#> 4    3    3
